{"key":"processedPost-12660207","value":{"id":12660207,"first":12659274,"last":12660207,"when":1275323107,"utime":"05/31/10 07:25 PM","cleanedPost":"If you fail to mist enough, your substrates will dry out.&nbsp; If you mist too much, they will waterlog.&nbsp; It's a judgment and visual call that each grower has to make.&nbsp; With experience, you'll develop a feel for just how&nbsp; much.&nbsp; A properly built shotgun terrarium will take care of fresh air exchange on its own, but there's never harm in fanning it out whenever you mist, which should be a light misting a few times per day, rather than one big soaking.<br />RR"}}